    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-15T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-15T10:00:00-05:00" n="391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/229: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ives</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-15T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 15, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 15—2:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Department’s 93, April 15, 6 p.m., to the Embassy, Paris [<hi rend="italic"
                        >London</hi>], I am in receipt of a note, dated May 14th, signed by Minister
                    of Foreign Affairs, wherein it is stated that Denmark, by the declaration made
                    on April 16, last, by the Chairman of the International Relief Bond Committee,
                    has renounced its liens upon the revenues of the Austrian Government derived
                    from customs and tobacco monopoly, on the condition that the Hague agreement of
                    January 20, 1930, come into force and that a similar renunciation is made by the
                    United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ives</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
